Privacy Policy for TronoTales
Effective Date: September 26, 2025

Privacy Policy
This app does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.
Usernames are freely chosen by the players and are used only locally on the device.
No data is processed, analyzed, or shared externally.
The camera is accessed solely to scan QR codes printed on official TronoTales game cards.
No camera images, scan data, or other information are transmitted, stored, or saved.
All app features function entirely offline.
GDPR Compliance:
This app does not process personal data as defined by the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
No user profiles, analytics tools, or third-party tracking technologies are used.
Third-Party Services:
If this app is downloaded from a third-party platform (e.g., Apple App Store or Google Play Store), please note that those services may apply their own data and privacy policies. TronoTales is not responsible for the content, data practices, or terms of such third parties.
